Edition:
Quote: <i>clobbering machine, the</i> the way in which the system is alleged to command conformity by squashing people who stand out, cutting tall poppies down to everybody's size, the tyranny of the mediocre, the dark side of egalitarianism - or sour grapes from those frustrated by conformity or slowed down by rules and regulations. Somewhat dated by Rogernomics.
